@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{anki-editor-extras.el} extends @samp{anki-editor}, the Emacs package for creating and managing Anki flashcards from Org mode. While @samp{anki-editor} handles the core workflow of defining notes as Org headings and pushing them to Anki via AnkiConnect, this extras package addresses several gaps in that workflow.

The package provides three main areas of functionality:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Duplicate management.} When Anki flags duplicate notes, the package offers an interactive workflow to review each flagged note, classify it as a real or false duplicate, and suspend the confirmed duplicates (@ref{Duplicate management}).
@item
@strong{Film plot summaries.} For users who maintain a bibliographic database with @samp{ebib}, the package can generate AI-written plot summaries for films, insert them as Org headings with the correct Anki properties, and push them to Anki in a single step (@ref{Plot summaries}).
@item
@strong{Card positioning.} The package provides commands to set the @samp{due} position of new cards, controlling where they appear in the review queue (@ref{Card positioning}).
@end itemize

Additionally, the package patches @samp{anki-editor-note-at-point} to handle a common edge case where the ``Basic'' Anki model has extra fields (e.g. ``Meta'') that cause the default field-mapping logic to fail (@ref{Basic note patch}).

The package depends on @samp{anki-editor}, @samp{gptel} (for AI-generated plot summaries), and @samp{ebib-extras} (for Bib@TeX{} metadata lookups).

