@node @code{anki-editor-extras-duplicates-field}
@section @code{anki-editor-extras-duplicates-field}

@vindex anki-editor-extras-duplicates-field
The user option @code{anki-editor-extras-duplicates-field} specifies which Anki note field is used to identify duplicates. This should match the field you select in Anki's ``Notes -> Find duplicates'' dialog. For example, if you check for duplicates based on the front side of your cards, set this to @samp{"Front"}.

The default value is the string @samp{"Front"}. You would change this if your primary note type uses a different field name for the content you want to deduplicate against.

