@node Basic note patch
@section Basic note patch

@findex anki-editor-note-at-point-a
The function @code{anki-editor-note-at-point-a} is an @samp{:around} advice on @code{anki-editor-note-at-point} that handles a common failure mode. When the ``Basic'' Anki model has additional fields beyond ``Front'' and ``Back'' (e.g. a ``Meta'' field), the default implementation raises an error because it cannot map the extra fields to Org subheadings.

The advice intercepts this error and falls back to a simpler mapping: the Org heading (or the @samp{ANKI_FIELD_FRONT} property, if set) becomes the ``Front'' field, the entry body becomes the ``Back'' field, and any additional model fields are set to empty strings. If the @samp{ANKI_FIELD_FRONT} property is present and non-blank, it always takes precedence, bypassing the error entirely.

This patch is applied automatically when the package is loaded.

@node Tag and card operations
@section Tag and card operations

@findex anki-editor-extras-remove-tag-from-query
@findex anki-editor-extras-suspend-cards-by-query
The function @code{anki-editor-extras-remove-tag-from-query} removes a given tag from all notes matching an Anki search query. It is used internally by the cleanup step of the duplicate workflow (@ref{Cleanup}) but can be called programmatically for other bulk tag operations.

The function @code{anki-editor-extras-suspend-cards-by-query} suspends all cards belonging to notes that match an Anki search query. It first retrieves the matching note IDs, then looks up their card IDs, and finally issues a suspend call via AnkiConnect. It reports how many cards and notes were affected.

